The economic cluster has wrapped up its detailed plans for the level-three lockdown. The country will see more economic sectors open up from Monday. JOHANNESBURG - Ministers of the economic cluster who serve in the National Coronavirus Command Council (NCCC) will brief the media on Level 3 lockdown regulations. This follows a briefing by the NCCC on Thursday. READ: Economic impact of lockdown will linger for years: experts President Cyril Ramaphosa announced on Sunday that the whole of the country would move to Level 3 from next week. South Africa is supporting the AU's call for a two-year debt standstill for poor indebted countries. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.